 the growth of the cathedral in the city as well as the evolution of sacred places within the cathedral itself. He goes on to consider this substantial monument in terms of its location in Toledo, Spain's most cosmopolitan city in the medieval period. Nickson also addresses the importance and symbolic significance of Toledo's cathedral to the city and the art and architecture of the medieval Iberian Peninsula, showing how it fits in with broader narratives of change in the arts, culture, and ideology of the late medieval period in Spain and in Mediterranean Europe as a whole.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aArchitecture, GothicxSpainxToledo. 0aArchitecture, GothiczSpainzToledo. 0aCathedralsxHistoryxTo 1500xSpainxToledo. 0aCathedralszSpainzToledoxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aChristian art and symbolismxMedieval, 500-1500xSpainxToledo. 0aChristian art and symbolismzSpainzToledoyMedieval, 500-1500. 7aART / History / Medieval.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311074525240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271076638423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780271076638.jpg  a978-3-11-074525-2  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK